title: Searchers find missing SA teenager injured
text:
Search finds missing SA teenager Connor Wilson injured Updated February 01, 2017 11:41:53 Map: Tantanoola 5280 
A search of pine forests in the south-east of South Australia has found a teenager safe but slightly injured after he had been missing for almost a day. 
Police, local residents and State Emergency Services volunteers began a search for 16-year-old Connor Wilson, after he left his home at Tantanoola on Tuesday afternoon on his motorbike but failed to arrive at work in the evening. 
Two aircraft were called in to bolster the search on Wednesday morning, with authorities expressing fears the teenager might have had an accident. 
Police said locals found the boy mid-morning on Wednesday near Burrungule Road and paramedics treated him for a leg injury.
